<subpara id="RM0000030JI02CX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM0000030JI02CX_01_0017" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001VQ00000">
<ptxt>RECOVER REFRIGERANT FROM REFRIGERATION SYSTEM
</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Start the engine.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Operate the cooler compressor under the conditions shown below:</ptxt>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Item</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Engine Speed</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Idling</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Operating Time</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>3 minutes or more</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>A/C Switch Status</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>On</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Blower Switch Status</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>HI</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Set Temperature</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>MAX COOL</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
<ptxt>This causes most of the compressor oil from the various components of the A/C system to collect in the A/C compressor.</ptxt>
<atten3>
<ptxt>It is not necessary to operate the cooler compressor if the A/C does not operate because of compressor lock, etc.</ptxt>
</atten3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Stop the engine.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Recover the refrigerant from the A/C system using a refrigerant recovery unit.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Use the refrigerant recovery unit in accordance with the manufacturer's instruction manual.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
</content1></s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000030JI02CX_01_0016" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00004DI00000">
<ptxt>REMOVE NO. 1 PRESSURE SWITCH</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Disconnect the connector.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a 27 mm deep socket wrench, remove the No. 1 pressure switch.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E226909" width="2.775699831in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the O-ring from the No. 1 pressure switch.</ptxt>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Seal the openings of the disconnected parts using vinyl tape to prevent moisture and foreign matter from entering them.</ptxt>
</atten3>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
